This paper discusses a privacy framework that involves a game between data holders and attackers, which is a common topic in the computer security (cs.CR) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of linear and nonlinear transformations, which are common in machine learning (cs.LG) and data science (cs.DS). The paper also involves optimization (cs.IT) and the use of neural networks (cs.AI).
